metadata.name: Wildfire
metadata.description:
Prevent wildfires/save animals

Since 2000, an annual average of 70,600 wildfires has burned an annual average of 7.0 million acres.

What causes a wildfire? Common causes of wildfires include lightning, human carelessness, arson, volcano eruption, and pyroclastic cloud from active volcano. Heat waves, droughts, and cyclical climate changes...
